"title": "5508: ruins",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5508",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The remains of a city, town or building after destruction or neglect. In Scripture it mainly describes the aftermath of divine judgment.</p>\n<h2>Israel's reduction to ruins</h2>\n<h3>As a covenant curse for disobeying God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:27-Lev26:33\">LEV 26:27–26:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut13:16\">DEU 13:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:49-Deut28:52\">DEU 28:49–28:52</a></p>\n<h3>The ruin prophesied</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:11\">JER 9:11</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic1:6-Mic1:7\">MIC 1:6–1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:5-Isa5:7\">ISA 5:5–5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:11-Isa6:13\">ISA 6:11–6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:7\">JER 4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:20\">JER 4:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:23-Jer4:26\">JER 4:23–4:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:5\">JER 22:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek6:6-Ezek6:7\">EZK 6:6–6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek6:14\">EZK 6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek21:27\">EZK 21:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:13-Amos3:15\">AMO 3:13–3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos7:9\">AMO 7:9</a></p>\n<h3>The ruin described</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:8-2Kgs25:15\">2KI 25:8–25:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:17-2Chr36:19\">2CH 36:17–36:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer39:8-Jer39:10\">JER 39:8–39:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:12-Jer52:19\">JER 52:12–52:19</a></p>\n<h3>The ruin lamented</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:39-Ps89:41\">PSA 89:39–89:41</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:3\">PSA 74:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:12-Ps80:16\">PSA 80:12–80:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:8-Isa64:12\">ISA 64:8–64:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:5-Lam2:9\">LAM 2:5–2:9</a></p>\n<h3>The ruin explained</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:2-Jer44:6\">JER 44:2–44:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:23-Ezek33:29\">EZK 33:23–33:29</a></p>\n<h2>Restoration of Israel's ruins</h2>\n<h3>Restoration of the ruins prophesied</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:3\">ISA 51:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:4\">ISA 61:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:24-Isa44:26\">ISA 44:24–44:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:12\">ISA 58:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:18-Jer30:19\">JER 30:18–30:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:27-Jer31:28\">JER 31:27–31:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:8-Ezek36:12\">EZK 36:8–36:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:33-Ezek36:36\">EZK 36:33–36:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:11-Amos9:12\">AMO 9:11–9:12</a></p>\n<h3>Restoration of the ruins fulfilled at the return from exile</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:1-Ezra3:13\">EZR 3:1–3:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:3-Neh1:4\">NEH 1:3–1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh2:11-Neh2:20\">NEH 2:11–2:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:1-Hag1:15\">HAG 1:1–1:15</a></p>\n<h2>Ruins through God's judgment on Israel's enemies</h2>\n<h3>Assyria</h3>\n<p>Nineveh was the capital of Assyria:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:7\">NAM 3:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph2:13-Zeph2:15\">ZEP 2:13–2:15</a></p>\n<h3>Babylon</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:19-Isa13:22\">ISA 13:19–13:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa23:13\">ISA 23:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:37\">JER 51:37</a></p>\n<h3>Edom</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek35:1-Ezek35:4\">EZK 35:1–35:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek35:9\">EZK 35:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:2-Mal1:4\">MAL 1:2–1:4</a></p>\n<h3>Egypt</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:19\">JER 46:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek29:8-Ezek29:12\">EZK 29:8–29:12</a></p>\n<h3>Moab</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:1\">JER 48:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:18\">JER 48:18</a></p>\n<h3>Philistia</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph2:4-Zeph2:6\">ZEP 2:4–2:6</a></p>\n<h3>Tyre</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:3-Ezek26:4\">EZK 26:3–26:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:11-Ezek26:14\">EZK 26:11–26:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:19-Ezek26:21\">EZK 26:19–26:21</a></p>\n<h2>Towns and sites ruined</h2>\n<h3>In warfare</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:24-Josh8:29\">JOS 8:24–8:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr20:1\">1CH 20:1</a></p>\n<h3>In natural disaster</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:6-Joel1:12\">JOL 1:6–1:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:16-Joel1:17\">JOL 1:16–1:17</a></p>\n<h2>Apocalyptic prophecies of ruin</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa24:1-Isa24:13\">ISA 24:1–24:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa27:9-Isa27:10\">ISA 27:9–27:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:17-Rev16:21\">REV 16:17–16:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:21-Rev18:23\">REV 18:21–18:23</a></p>\n<h2>Repairs to the ruined temple, altar and defences</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:30\">1KI 18:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs12:1-2Kgs12:12\">2KI 12:1–12:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:4-2Chr24:13\">2CH 24:4–24:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:3-2Kgs22:7\">2KI 22:3–22:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:8-2Chr34:13\">2CH 34:8–34:13</a></p>\n<h2>Proverbial references to ruins</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:28\">PRO 25:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job3:13-Job3:14\">JOB 3:13–3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:27-Job15:28\">JOB 15:27–15:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:6\">PSA 102:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:30-Prov24:31\">PRO 24:30–24:31</a></p>",
